{"lemma":"سِمْسِم","slug":"سِمْسِم","root":"س.م.س.م","root_slug":"س-م-س-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-س-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20592","n20606","n20607","n20608"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%85"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sesame (plant or seed)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Simsim, Semsem (a former village in what is now Israel)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Semitic *šamn-\nAkkadian šaman\nAkkadian šammum\nAkkadian 𒊭𒈦𒌑𒈬 (šamaššammum)bor.\nAramaic שׁוּמְשֻׁומָא (šumššumā)bor.\nArabic سمسم\nBorrowed from Aramaic שׁוּמְשֻׁומָא (šumššumā), borrowed from Akkadian 𒊭𒈦𒌑𒈬 (šamaššammum), from šaman + šammum. Compare Classical Syriac ܫܘܫܡܐ (šūšmāʾ, šuššəmāʾ)."},"ipa":["/sim.sim/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20592","headword_ar":"سَمْسَمَ","root":"sm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went along, gently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a fox)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran in a certain manner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosamapN","text_ar":"سَمْسَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TK:) the latter signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) of the fox. (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TK","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n20606","headword_ar":"سَمْسَمٌ","root":"sm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~N","text_ar":"سَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence.       -A2-  It is also an epithet, of which only the fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", is mentioned: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAmN","text_ar":"سَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosamN","text_ar":"سَمْسَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosaAmN","text_ar":"سَمْسَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amosamu","text_ar":"السَّمْسَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amosaAmu","text_ar":"السَّمْسَامُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) [the latter erroneously written in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imAm","text_ar":"السِّمام"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wolf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) because of his lightness, or activity, or agility: (M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amosamu","text_ar":"السَّمْسَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wolf that is small in the body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amosamu","text_ar":"السَّمْسَمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fox;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samosamN","text_ar":"سَمْسَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~umaAsimu","text_ar":"السُّمَاسِمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20607","headword_ar":"سُمْسُمٌ","root":"sm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAmN","text_ar":"سَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence, in three places.       -A2-  Also, the former, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simosimN","text_ar":"سِمْسِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the latter is a mistake, [ascribed in the K to J,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Red ants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sumosumapN","text_ar":"سُمْسُمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simosimapN","text_ar":"سِمْسِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain insect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a red ant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAmapN","text_ar":"سَمَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an insect of the form of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aklp","text_ar":"اكلة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namolap","text_ar":"نَمْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ant"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a red colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Az says, I have seen it in the desert, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it bites,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stings, painfully:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAsimu","text_ar":"سَمَاسِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) said by Aboo-Kheyreh to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain things found in El-Basrah, that bite vehemently, having longish heads, and the colours of which incline to redness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samaAsimu","text_ar":"سَمَاسِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below."}],"source_refs":["K","M","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20608","headword_ar":"سِمْسِمٌ","root":"sm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sesame; sesamum orientale"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.; applied in the present day to the plant and its grain;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known grain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) it is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunojudo","text_ar":"كُنْجُدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA, KL;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"julojulaAnN","text_ar":"جُلْجُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) said by AHn to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant in the Saráh"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~araAp","text_ar":"السَّرَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and El-Yemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) [by this is evidently here meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sesame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"both;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though it also signifies the “ fruit of the coriander; ” for otherwise, the most commonly-known meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simosimN","text_ar":"سِمْسِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"would be unmentioned in the M;] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~","text_ar":"حَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain from which the oil called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~","text_ar":"حَلّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is expressed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K; [by the author of the latter of which, this was evidently understood to be different from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"julojulaAn","text_ar":"جُلْجُلَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is mentioned by him after the description of properties here following;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is glutinous, corruptive to the stomach and the mouth; but is rendered good by honey; and when it is digested, it fattens; and the washing of the hair with the water in which its leaves have been cooked lengthens and improves it: the wild sort thereof is known by the name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalobahanok","text_ar":"جَلْبَهَنْك"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) thus, with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sukoon to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", [but written in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalobahanako","text_ar":"جَلْبَهَنَكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] a Pers. word, [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jlobahanoG","text_ar":"جلْبَهَنْگ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] arabicized; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its action is nearly like that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarobaq","text_ar":"خَرْبَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hellebore"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes from half a drachm to a drachm is administered to him who is affected with palsy, and he is cured thereby,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speedily;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but a drachm thereof is dangerous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a great degree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imosimu AlhinodiY~u","text_ar":"السِّمْسِمُ الهِنْدِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xirowaEN","text_ar":"خِرْوَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrE","text_ar":"خرع"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain creeping thing resembling it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See also the next preceding paragraph, where it and its n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"are mentioned."}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}